16:17.544 --> 16:19.046
I didn't see a dog all day.

16:19.079 --> 16:21.014
Well, on TV, sure.

16:21.048 --> 16:22.449
You can't turn on a TV

16:22.482 --> 16:24.517
without seeing, like,
or four of them shits.

16:24.551 --> 16:26.319
(clears throat)

16:26.353 --> 16:27.554
(music stops)

16:27.587 --> 16:30.623
Hello. Thank you all for coming
to the memorial service

16:30.657 --> 16:33.193
for my father,
Ronny Overly.

16:33.226 --> 16:35.062
His friend Freddie
will do the eulogy,

16:35.095 --> 16:37.064
we'll toast,
and then you will leave.

16:37.097 --> 16:39.066
(Freddie claps,
piano plays upbeat tune)

16:39.099 --> 16:41.734
Cheers.

16:41.768 --> 16:43.870
Cheers, everyone.
(piano plays flourish)

16:43.903 --> 16:45.905
"Ronny Overly

16:45.938 --> 16:47.640
"was not only my coworker.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.342
"He was my hero.

16:49.376 --> 16:51.711
"He cherished his family,

16:51.744 --> 16:54.047
"especially his son, Jimmy.

16:54.081 --> 16:55.548
"I remember when

16:55.582 --> 16:57.084
"I came out to visit Jimmy.

16:57.117 --> 17:00.019
"Oh, bloody hell.

17:00.053 --> 17:01.654
"This was supposed to be
in the third person.

17:01.688 --> 17:04.691
"Oh, well. Ha, ha.
It's me, Ronny.

17:04.724 --> 17:09.028
"I wrote this in pen,
so I might as well keep going.

17:09.062 --> 17:11.164
"I just realized

17:11.198 --> 17:13.366
"Freddie has to read
whatever I say.

17:13.400 --> 17:15.168
"My name is Freddie,

17:15.202 --> 17:17.036
and I'm a..."

17:17.070 --> 17:18.538
I'm not reading that.

17:18.571 --> 17:19.939
Skipping forward.

17:19.972 --> 17:21.708
"Anyway,

17:21.741 --> 17:24.377
"I did my best to love him,
but he rejected me.

17:24.411 --> 17:27.714
"I sent him presents,
I visited,

17:27.747 --> 17:29.249
"I Facebook-requested him.

17:29.282 --> 17:31.851
"Anyway, I forgive him.

17:31.884 --> 17:33.453
"Please scatter my ashes

17:33.486 --> 17:36.256
"at the home of actor
Tony Shalhoub,

17:36.289 --> 17:39.392
"whose movie Big Night
you and I attended together.

17:39.426 --> 17:41.628
What's that, Fi?"

17:41.661 --> 17:43.130
WOMAN (whispering):
I think it's "Shalhoub."

17:43.163 --> 17:44.731
"Your sister just told me
he's a Paki.

17:44.764 --> 17:46.866
"Shit. Anyway,

17:46.899 --> 17:49.702
"after the movie, you turned
to me and said, 'That's what

17:49.736 --> 17:51.638
"'I want to do, Daddy.

17:51.671 --> 17:53.273
"I want to tell stories.'

17:53.306 --> 17:56.743
"And I said,
'You can do anything

17:56.776 --> 17:58.478
"you want, son.'

17:58.511 --> 18:00.947
"And so, you became a writer.

18:00.980 --> 18:02.949
"I did that.

18:02.982 --> 18:05.084
"Anyway, I hope you ditch

18:05.118 --> 18:06.553
"that depressed girl.

18:06.586 --> 18:08.888
(gasps quietly)
"And I hope Fi is wrong about

18:08.921 --> 18:10.423
"Tony Shalhoub.

18:10.457 --> 18:12.625
"Looking at his last name now,

18:12.659 --> 18:14.794
"it does look suspicious.

18:14.827 --> 18:16.829
"Shal-houb.

18:16.863 --> 18:18.831
Cheers."

18:18.865 --> 18:21.168
(piano plays upbeat tune)

18:21.201 --> 18:23.203
(quiet murmuring)

18:25.538 --> 18:28.441
Excuse me! Excuse me.
We are not done.

18:28.475 --> 18:30.277
First of all,
he is a liar!

18:30.310 --> 18:32.679
I begged him
to take me to Big Night

18:32.712 --> 18:34.347
so that we could bond,
but instead,

18:34.381 --> 18:36.283
he went to D3: The Mighty Ducks,

18:36.316 --> 18:37.984
and I watched Big Night alone.

18:38.017 --> 18:39.786
Then his movie was shorter,

18:39.819 --> 18:42.155
he forgot that I was with him,
so he left without me.

18:42.189 --> 18:46.493
For him to claim that he was
rejected after 18 years

18:46.526 --> 18:50.397
of constant rejection
on his part is crazy!

18:51.998 --> 18:54.100
In fact...

18:54.133 --> 18:56.503
(piano plays dramatic tune)

19:00.540 --> 19:02.809
I've prepared a list of heckles
for the occasion.

19:02.842 --> 19:04.211
VERNON:
Sweet.

19:04.244 --> 19:07.314
Uh, "Dad, fortunately,
your death wasn't too much

19:07.347 --> 19:09.382
"of a shock, considering
you already look like

19:09.416 --> 19:11.017
"someone put a Manchester jersey

19:11.050 --> 19:13.353
on the corpse
of a drowned person."

19:13.386 --> 19:15.154
(piano plays dramatic flourish)

19:15.188 --> 19:17.824
"Dad, you always were
a lady killer.

19:17.857 --> 19:20.026
"You gave all three
of my sisters genes

19:20.059 --> 19:22.061
"for alcoholism,
learning disabilities

19:22.094 --> 19:24.331
and morbid obesity."

19:24.364 --> 19:25.965
(laughs)
Ugh.

19:25.998 --> 19:27.900
I mean, we are talking
about a guy who was

19:27.934 --> 19:31.371
so narcissistic
that he wrote his own eulogy!

19:31.404 --> 19:33.206
What's next?!

19:33.240 --> 19:34.941
Are we...?

19:36.943 --> 19:39.579
Freddie, when did my dad
find out he was dying?

19:39.612 --> 19:42.715
He was diagnosed
some time last year.

19:53.360 --> 19:55.262
(piano plays upbeat tune)

19:55.295 --> 19:57.163
BEN:
Hey, folks,

19:57.196 --> 19:59.165
if, uh, you're gonna
Instagram this,

19:59.198 --> 20:02.535
be sure to, uh, hashtag
"BenFoldsSightings,"

20:02.569 --> 20:05.838
"BenFoldsIsEverywhere"
and "BenFoldsMovesToLA."

20:05.872 --> 20:09.276
If you do, I'll personally tell
you what Brick is really about.

20:09.309 --> 20:10.443
Abortion.

20:10.477 --> 20:12.779
No.
(plays upbeat tune)

20:23.222 --> 20:24.457
Hey, thanks for playing.

20:24.491 --> 20:25.925
You were really great.
(door opens)

20:25.958 --> 20:27.794
Ben! Ben! Over here, Ben!

20:27.827 --> 20:28.961
Over here, Ben!
Sorry.

20:28.995 --> 20:30.730
Not an appropriate
venue, bud.

20:30.763 --> 20:32.932
Now, I'll take some pictures
with you outside later.

20:32.965 --> 20:33.800
All right?

20:33.833 --> 20:35.568
Uh...

20:35.602 --> 20:37.136
Wasn't that
the same guy

20:37.169 --> 20:39.372
who asked for your autograph
at the ice cream place?

20:39.406 --> 20:42.975
What?! A paparazzi
and an autograph reseller?

20:43.009 --> 20:44.844
Scumbag.

20:47.146 --> 20:50.216
Okay, look, I moved to L.A.
a couple months ago,

20:50.249 --> 20:54.321
and, you know, everyone was so
excited when Moby moved to town.

20:54.354 --> 20:56.489
It was like,
"Moby bought that house.

20:56.523 --> 20:58.625
Oh, and Moby
opened that restaurant."

20:58.658 --> 21:02.228
Ben Folds moved to town? Bupkis.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.263
That's...

21:04.297 --> 21:07.500
That's incredibly...

21:07.534 --> 21:09.936
clever... of you.

21:09.969 --> 21:11.270
But, hey,

21:11.304 --> 21:12.805
it's my job now.

21:12.839 --> 21:15.608
Well, this was fun. Hey, guys,

21:15.642 --> 21:17.944
want to hit Big Wang's
or something?

21:17.977 --> 21:19.111
Get a couple drinks in me,

21:19.145 --> 21:20.313
I might tell you
what Brick's about.

21:20.347 --> 21:21.581
Abortion.

21:21.614 --> 21:24.016
Goddamn it.
How'd that get out?

21:28.220 --> 21:30.222
*

21:47.374 --> 21:50.042
(quietly):
Oh, shit. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

21:50.076 --> 21:52.078
I'm sorry.

21:54.246 --> 21:56.549
JIMMY: You know, when we had
that moment in the pub,

21:56.583 --> 22:00.286
I thought to myself,
"After 33 years,

22:00.319 --> 22:04.524
I'm finally having
a real moment with my father."

22:04.557 --> 22:06.225
(scoffs)

22:06.258 --> 22:08.895
Can't believe what a fool I was.

22:08.928 --> 22:11.163
There wasn't a shred of truth
in that moment.

22:11.197 --> 22:13.165
You were lying the whole time.

22:13.199 --> 22:16.403
You were dying,
you didn't say a word.

22:16.436 --> 22:20.072
All you had to do was say,
"Hey, Jimmy,

22:20.106 --> 22:23.376
"this might be the last time
I get to see you.

22:25.077 --> 22:28.147
Is there anything
you'd like to say?"

22:28.180 --> 22:30.517
And that way...

22:30.550 --> 22:35.422
despite decades of
neglecting, withholding,

22:35.455 --> 22:38.357
general assholery,

22:38.391 --> 22:41.794
I could have had
a modicum of closure.

22:43.963 --> 22:45.665
Goddamn you!

22:45.698 --> 22:49.669
I can hear you laughing at
the world "modicum" as I speak.

22:49.702 --> 22:52.572
Well, guess what.

22:52.605 --> 22:54.907
I'm getting my closure
right now.

22:56.909 --> 23:00.246
You do not get
to affect me anymore!

23:02.081 --> 23:04.283
So long, Dad.

23:05.317 --> 23:06.753
(grunts)

23:06.786 --> 23:09.456
* The captain runs his ship

23:09.489 --> 23:11.190
(crying)
* Into the rocks

23:11.223 --> 23:13.560
* Well, should we give him

23:13.593 --> 23:18.431
* A second chance with birth
and dying based on chance *

23:18.465 --> 23:20.733
* The first mate tried in vain

23:20.767 --> 23:24.070
* To reason with his leader

23:24.103 --> 23:26.372
* But he failed
to heed the warning *

23:26.405 --> 23:30.409
* Now there's wreckage
in the morning *

23:30.443 --> 23:35.548
* The ocean floor is filled
with forgotten gold *

23:35.582 --> 23:38.585
* And the tears
of fallen captains *

23:38.618 --> 23:42.889
* Keep the salty waters full

23:42.922 --> 23:45.492
* And you might
think his folly *

23:45.525 --> 23:48.227
* Obvious and blind

23:48.260 --> 23:51.263
* But who among us
hasn't needed *

23:51.297 --> 23:55.502
* Judgment tossed aside,
oh, no. *

23:56.503 --> 23:59.438
(dog barks)

